const schemaJson = `<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Service","dateModified":"2026-05-04","name":"Order Pick and Pack Ukraine — Scan-Based 3PL with 99.5% Accuracy","description":"Pick and pack fulfillment from Ukrainian 3PL warehouse for international e-commerce brands. WMS-routed pickers, scan-based picking at pick AND pack stages, QC checkpoint before package seal. 47-second average per order, 99.5% verified accuracy, $0.41 per pick all-in pricing. 3,700 m² warehouse, 60,000 shipments per month, 0 days down since February 2022.","provider":{"@type":"Organization","name":"MTP Group Fulfillment","legalName":"LLC \\"MTP Group Fulfillment\\"","taxID":"45315740","foundingDate":"2023-10-02","url":"https://www.fulfillmentmtp.com.ua","telephone":"+380501444645"},"areaServed":[{"@type":"Country","name":"UA"},{"@type":"Country","name":"PL"},{"@type":"Country","name":"DE"},{"@type":"Country","name":"CZ"},{"@type":"Country","name":"US"},{"@type":"Country","name":"CA"}],"serviceType":"International Pick and Pack Fulfillment from Ukraine","audience":{"@type":"BusinessAudience","name":"International e-commerce brands using Ukraine as low-cost fulfillment base, indie publishers, D2C subscription boxes, EU and US sellers exploring Eastern Europe 3PL"},"offers":{"@type":"Offer","priceCurrency":"USD","price":"0.41","description":"Pick and pack — $0.41 per order at 200+ daily volume (typical 3-4 SKU order). Equivalent 18 UAH locally. Minimum monthly fee 5,000 UAH (~$120) for first 3 months."}}</script>
<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is pick and pack in 3PL fulfillment?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Pick and pack is the operation where a fulfillment center picks SKUs off warehouse shelves according to a customer order, then packs those SKUs into a shipping box or mailer with appropriate dunnage for safe transit. In standard 3PL pricing, pick and pack is often billed as separate line items (pick fee + pack fee + handling fee). MTP bundles all stages into a single per-order tariff ($0.41 at 200+ daily volume) including WMS routing, two-stage scan verification, QC checkpoint, label printing, and carrier handover — no hidden surcharges."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is acceptable pick accuracy in 3PL?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Industry standard for 3PL with WMS and scan-based picking is 99.5-99.8%. Without WMS and scan verification, typical accuracy drops to 95-97%. The gap between 99% and 99.5% sounds small but represents a 5x difference in error count (50 errors per 1,000 orders vs 5). MTP measures actual accuracy at 99.72% in the previous quarter, achieved through four independent verification layers: WMS-routed picking (no manual search), pick-stage barcode scan (blocks wrong SKU at the shelf), pack-stage scan (second independent verification at packing), and QC checkpoint for high-value or multi-SKU orders."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does scan-based picking work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Scan-based picking means every SKU is verified by barcode scan at the moment it leaves the shelf. The picker carries a handheld scanner connected to the WMS. When picking a SKU, the picker scans its barcode — the WMS compares the scanned code to the expected SKU for the order. Match means green light, proceed. Mismatch means the WMS blocks the operation and forces the picker to return the wrong item and find the correct one. This eliminates the entire class of errors where a picker accidentally takes a similar-looking SKU from a nearby bin. Pack-stage scan repeats the verification at the packing station — second independent layer."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the difference between pick and pack?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Pick is the act of retrieving SKUs from warehouse storage according to a customer order. Pack is the act of placing those picked SKUs into a shipping container (box, polymailer, padded envelope) with appropriate void fill or dunnage for safe transit. In 3PL pricing models, pick and pack are often charged as separate operations with separate per-line-item or per-box fees. MTP combines both into a single bundled per-order tariff to make pricing predictable and transparent — one number in your invoice instead of three."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who pays for picking errors in 3PL?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"At MTP, picking errors are our liability. When a confirmed error occurs (customer photo evidence + WMS log showing who picked the order and when), we ship the correct item to the customer at our cost, retrieve the wrong item from the customer at our cost, and reimburse the merchant for the original shipping and reverse logistics fees. SLA for incident closure is 24 hours from customer report to corrected re-shipment. This is documented in the contract with material liability — not a marketing promise but a legal obligation. WMS logs serve as the audit trail; if the log shows the scan was performed and the barcode matched, the error is on the supplier side (mislabeled product) and root cause analysis is shared with the merchant."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why does Ukraine pick and pack cost $0.41 vs $1.50 US baseline?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Three structural factors. First, warehouse rent in the Kyiv metro area runs roughly 60-70% lower than equivalent US metro 3PL space ($4-6 per square meter vs $12-18 in US logistics hubs). Second, picker labor cost is approximately 65% lower than US warehouse worker wages at equivalent skill level (Ukrainian pickers earn $400-800 monthly vs $2,400-3,600 US baseline). Third, MTP bundles pick + pack + handling + QC into one per-order tariff instead of stacking separate fees common in US 3PL pricing models. Combined, this gives $0.41 per order at 200+ daily volume vs the typical $1.20-1.80 US 3PL baseline for equivalent service quality. Quality is not compromised — 99.5% accuracy with two-stage scan is industry standard or better."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Ukrainian fulfillment reliable for international shipping during wartime?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"MTP has shipped 60,000 orders monthly with zero days of fulfillment downtime since February 2022. Both warehouse facilities (Shchaslyve 2,700 m² and Bilohorodka 1,000 m²) operate with backup power generators, Starlink redundant internet, and on-site fuel reserves. War-related infrastructure attacks have caused brief operational adjustments but never order delivery delays beyond carrier transit times. International shipments via Nova Poshta International, Meest, and DHL continue operating with stable transit times: Poland 5-7 days, Germany 7-10, USA 14-25, Canada 14-21. War-resilience is a structural differentiator vs Western 3PL where operational continuity is assumed but rarely battle-tested."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the minimum order volume for Ukraine pick and pack?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Minimum monthly fee is 5,000 UAH (~$120) for the first 3 months, equivalent to approximately 30-40 daily orders. There is no fixed lower bound on SKU count or order size. Small subscription brands shipping 30 orders daily, indie publishers fulfilling 50-print runs, and D2C startups testing market fit all use MTP at this entry tier. The economics flip in favor of outsourcing once the merchant calculates the cost of their own time — at 30 orders daily on a self-managed warehouse, the owner typically spends 4-6 hours daily on pick and pack, equivalent to $1,200-2,400 monthly opportunity cost at $10/hour internal rate."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How fast can we onboard to MTP pick and pack?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"3-5 business days from contract signature to first picked order for catalogs under 1,000 SKU. Standard onboarding sequence: day 1-2 contract execution and SKU catalog handover, day 2-3 inbound receiving and address-storage placement on shelves, day 3-4 API integration with merchant CRM (Shopify, WooCommerce, Etsy, Amazon Seller Central, custom REST API), day 4-5 end-to-end test order and go-live confirmation. Larger catalogs (1,000-10,000 SKU) take 7-10 days for the inbound and slotting phase. International merchants can ship inbound inventory via standard freight forwarders to our Kyiv warehouse before contract signature to save onboarding time."}}]}</script>
