<section class="kz-sec kz-sec-light"><div class="ctr">
  <div class="kz-chip kz-chip-dark">FREQUENTLY ASKED</div>
  <h2 class="kz-h2">Pick and pack questions buyers ask before evaluating Ukraine 3PL</h2>
  <div class="kz-faq">
    <details><summary>What is pick and pack in 3PL fulfillment?</summary><p>Pick and pack is the operation where a fulfillment center retrieves SKUs from warehouse shelves per a customer order, then packs them into a shipping container with appropriate dunnage. In standard 3PL pricing, often billed as separate line items (pick fee + pack fee + handling fee). MTP bundles all stages into one per-order tariff ($0.41 at 200+ daily volume) including WMS routing, two-stage scan, QC checkpoint, label, and carrier handover.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What is acceptable pick accuracy in 3PL?</summary><p>Industry standard for 3PL with WMS and scan-based picking is 99.5-99.8%. Without WMS and scan, typical drops to 95-97%. The 0.5% gap represents a 5x error count difference (50 vs 5 errors per 1,000 orders). MTP measured 99.72% in the previous quarter through four verification layers.</p></details>
    <details><summary>How does scan-based picking work?</summary><p>Every SKU is verified by barcode scan when leaving the shelf. Picker carries handheld scanner connected to WMS. Scan compares to expected SKU — match proceeds, mismatch blocks. Pack-stage scan repeats verification at packing. Two independent layers eliminate the entire error class of "grabbed similar SKU from nearby bin."</p></details>
    <details><summary>What is the difference between pick and pack?</summary><p>Pick is retrieving SKUs from storage per order. Pack is placing them in shipping container with void fill. In 3PL pricing often charged separately. MTP bundles into single per-order tariff for predictable invoicing.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Who pays for picking errors in 3PL?</summary><p>At MTP, picking errors are our liability. Confirmed errors (customer photo + WMS log) trigger free reshipment of correct item, free return logistics, and merchant reimbursement for original shipping. SLA 24 hours from report to corrected shipment. Documented in contract with material liability — not marketing promise but legal obligation.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Why does Ukraine pick and pack cost $0.41 vs $1.50 US baseline?</summary><p>Three structural factors: warehouse rent 60-70% lower than US metro 3PL space, picker labor 65% lower than US warehouse wages at equivalent skill, bundled pricing instead of stacked fees common in US 3PL. Combined gives $0.41 vs $1.20-1.80 US baseline. Quality not compromised — 99.5% accuracy with two-stage scan is industry standard or better.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Is Ukrainian fulfillment reliable for international shipping during wartime?</summary><p>0 days of fulfillment downtime since February 2022, 60,000 orders monthly. Both warehouses operate with backup generators, Starlink redundant internet, on-site fuel reserves. International shipments (Nova Poshta International, Meest, DHL) continue with stable transit times: Poland 5-7 days, Germany 7-10, USA 14-25, Canada 14-21.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What is the minimum order volume for Ukraine pick and pack?</summary><p>Minimum monthly fee 5,000 UAH (~$120) for first 3 months, equivalent to ~30-40 daily orders. No fixed lower bound on SKU count. Small subscription brands, indie publishers, D2C startups all use MTP at this entry tier.</p></details>
    <details><summary>How fast can we onboard to MTP pick and pack?</summary><p>3-5 business days from contract to first picked order for catalogs under 1,000 SKU. Sequence: contract + SKU catalog handover, inbound receiving and address-storage, API integration, end-to-end test order, go-live. Larger catalogs (1,000-10,000 SKU) take 7-10 days.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What carriers do you ship through internationally?</summary><p>Nova Poshta International (Europe and select global), Meest (worldwide), DHL Express (premium global), USPS (US-bound), Ukrposhta International (cost-effective small parcels). Carrier choice configurable per order or per SKU category.</p></details>
  </div>
</div></section>

